<TEXT>
the scales of justice tipped against a 
350pound man who had claimed he was fired from his fastfood 
restaurant job for being too fat 
a us district judge on thursday rejected ted s mounts claim 
of discrimination by long john silvers inc and his request for 
205000 in damages 
mounts 37 said his obesity was a medical problem and therefore 
a physical handicap federal and state laws prohibit employment 
discrimination on the basis of race sex nationality religion and 
physical handicaps 
but judge charles haden said it would require some quantum 
leaps of logic to accept the discrimination argument attorneys 
for the restaurant where mounts worked for 12 years said he was 
fired in 1987 for incompetence not size 
mounts claimed that company officials harassed embarrassed 
and humiliated him because of his weight he was never 
reprimanded for his job performance but every written evaluation 
he received from 1980 to 1986 mentioned his size he said 
it was always an unwritten rule there that being big was 
bad mounts said they say i dont look professional being 
overweight 
mounts said he is unemployed and receives social security and 
state workers compensation benefits 
im not really happy about the decision but maybe it will 
encourage others in my situation to stand up and not be afraid of 
the big guy mounts said 
</TEXT>
