<TEXT>
the crumbling of communism is sweet vindication 
for soviet dissident natan sharansky who was whisked through the 
berlin wall in a 1986 prisoner exchange after languishing for nine 
years in the gulags 
the events of the last year were the realization of our 
wildest dreams there is such a hole in this iron wall that nobody 
can ever rebuild it again sharansky said there is no question 
communist ideology has failed and some of the most fascinating 
changes are happening in our lifetime 
sharansky 41 personifies the struggle of soviet jews for human 
rights and freer emigration he begins his first us lecture tour 
with a speech tuesday at the university of california at davis 
in an hourlong interview here sharansky said dissidents should 
get credit for forcing president mikhail gorbachev to restructure 
the soviet system he also said antisemitism in the soviet union 
is getting stronger as communisms grip weakens and is fueling an 
exodus of jews to israel 
for sharansky the breakdown of the old order in the soviet bloc 
was the most exciting moment since his release from prison after 
serving nine years of a 13year sentence for spying a charge that 
he denied 
we dissidents had such deep beliefs in our hearts that sooner 
or later this system had to become bankrupt morally socially 
economically and politically nobody could expect it to go so 
quickly he said 
i told my wife that that by the time our youngest daughter 
grew one tooth two more dictators in eastern europe had fallen 
down said sharansky who lives in israel with his wife and two 
daughters 
sharansky was at first denied permission to leave the soviet 
union although his wife avital was allowed to leave a day after 
they were married in 1974 she worked tirelessly for his freedom 
meeting with president reagan to plead his case reagan and 
gorbachev arranged for his release at a summit meeting and 
sharansky passed to freedom across glienicke bridge to west berlin 
on a frozen feb 11 1986 
sharansky recounted the horrors of soviet prisons in his 1988 
book fear no evil published by random house he plans about 10 
lectures a year to talk about who is responsible for soviet 
restructuring 
the soviet dissidents and their supporters in the west are the 
midwives of glasnost and perestroika sharansky said cautioning 
against the lionization of gorbachev as a champion of democracy 
gorbachev is a loyal communist his aim was to save the 
communist system by changing it he deserves credit for one thing 
he was the first soviet leader to say that communism would lose to 
capitalism if urgent changes werent made in the economy 
sharansky also said there are dissidents still in soviet 
prisons who were jailed for saying the same things as gorbachev 
sharansky was a comrade of soviet dissident and nobel 
prizewinning physicist andrei sakharov but was denied permission 
to visit the soviet union for sakharovs funeral in december 
sharansky who has a street marker in new york named after him 
dropped his soviet name anatoly to use his hebrew name natan 
when he entered israel 
as chairman of the soviet jewry zionist forum he helps soviet 
jews find housing and jobs 
we are seeing the biggest exodus of jews in modern history 
they are afraid to stay in the soviet union because of 
antisemitism its absolutely inevitable this exodus will 
continue sharansky said there is practically no place for 
jews in the soviet union in the future 
</TEXT>
