<TEXT>
a judge on friday threw out all charges 
against a couple accused of kidnapping their adult daughter in a 
failed deprogramming attempt saying a jury never would be able to 
reach any kind of verdict 
superior court judge david moon jrs ruling came a day after he 
declared a mistrial because a jury had been deadlocked on kidnap 
false imprisonment and battery charges against earle and dorothy 
brown both 58 of santa cruz 
the browns and three codefendants were charged with abducting 
ginger brown from a northern san diego county parking lot in may 
1988 and holding her for five days in an attempt to deprogram her 
ginger brown then 22 had joined a small religious group called 
great among nations which her parents say is a cult whose leader 
benjamin altschul brainwashes his followers 
also charged in the case were the browns other daughter holly 
brown 25 of san francisco los angeles deprogrammer cliff 
daniels 35 and his accomplice hank erler 23 of escondido 
a jury on wednesday had returned seven acquittals against the 
defendants but deadlocked on remaining charges 
the judge said that any further court proceedings would not be 
worth the time and expense he said the jury was unwilling to 
convict the defendants even though some of them incriminated 
themselves during testimony 
this judge is not going to let the peoples courtroom be used 
to titillate the publics fascination with unusual religious 
groups he said 
earle brown said he was delighted by the rulings and said he now 
wanted his daughter back 
weve since forgiven her if there is animosity toward us on 
her part we might apologize but i dont know what we might 
apologize for to the group we will still continue to pray for 
her he said 
ginger brown who remains a part of the religious group said 
she was not disappointed with the ruling and planned to drop a 25 
million civil suit against her parents and the other defendants 
i didnt lose anything other than the strong binding i had 
with my family that deprogrammer cliff daniels has been 
successful in wedging apart she said 
i hope they come to me and apologize come to all the members 
of my church and apologize and especially to my pastor and 
apologize for this slanderous way in which they have portrayed our 
ministry she said 
altschul has described his group as a television ministry that 
hopes to produce and sell programs to television stations worldwide 
