<TEXT>
the internal revenue service is toughening 
rules of conduct for senior employees following highly publicized 
allegations of misconduct by some field managers 
the aim said irs commissioner fred goldberg is to protect 
what is the bedrock of our tax system and that is the real and 
perceived integrity of this institution 
what we need is ongoing attention and adherence to the kinds 
of issues of conduct ethics and appearance that are essential to 
tax administration goldberg said friday in announcing the ethics 
initiative 
goldberg acted after congressional hearings last summer in which 
managers and other top officials of some field offices were accused 
of abusing power favoring friends and operating almost 
independently of directives from the agencys washington 
headquarters 
this is an agency of 120000 employees and we will rise or 
fall on the kinds of procedures the kinds of controls we have 
in place that minimize to the absolute extent possible incidents 
that create either the appearance or reality of illegality 
misjudgment or misconduct goldberg said 
the initiative was hailed by rep douglas barnard dga 
chairman of the house government operations consumer subcommittee 
which conducted a twoyear investigation of the allegations and 
held public hearings last year 
if that plan is properly implemented it will go a long way 
toward solving some extremely serious employee misconduct and 
morale problems at the service barnard said 
in order for our selfassessment tax system to work properly 
the public must be confident that senior irs employees are 
respectful of taxpayer rights and educated to exercising their 
responsibilities fairly as well as effectively barnard said 
in announcing the plan goldberg disclosed the irs has suspended 
at least temporarily a lockbox setup roundly criticized during 
barnards hearings that some have interpreted as an amnesty 
program for tax cheats 
the irs will be trying to clarify what if anything we want to 
do with the lockbox procedure goldberg said he denied that the 
procedure is necessarily an amnesty but acknowledged it could be 
interpreted as such 
the procedure was authorized by ronald saranow then head of the 
irs criminal investigation division in los angeles delinquent 
taxpayers represented by a lawyer friend of saranow could while 
keeping their identities secret make cash payments to a lockbox 
and receive an irs letter saying they would not be the subject of a 
criminal investigation unless their evasion arose from illegal 
activities 
in discussing the ethics initiative goldberg refused to answer 
questions about the most widely publicized allegation at the 
barnard hearings a charge that an irs executive launched an 
investigation of the manufacturers of jordache jeans because of his 
relationship with the competing makers of guess jeans 
in that probe the irs raided jordaches new york offices and 
seized one million documents the company has not been charged 
the new ethics program announced by goldberg includes 
an agreement under which the treasury department inspector 
general will investigate allegations against senior irs managers 
and all employees of the irs inspection division employees in that 
division operate as the internal affairs branch of irs 
an inspection hotline to give irs field employees a direct 
line to washington headquarters when they dont feel comfortable 
complaining to local officials 
reversal of an earlier decision under which local office 
managers can approve their own travel vouchers 
removing any ambiguity from regulations on investments by irs 
employees 
ensuring that every training program for irs employees includes 
emphasis on ethics and conduct 
</TEXT>
