<TEXT>
here is a brief look at the long 
duration exposure facility satellite which has been in space for 
nearly six years 
ldef carries coating and thermal systems experiments five 
power and propulsion experiments 17 science experiments 14 
electronics and optics experiments and 21 materials used in space 
flight including metals graphite epoxies polymers resins and 
thermal coatings scientists want to know if materials strength 
properties changed and if mechanical systems still work 
experts will also study the satellites frame bolts 
batteries and electric motors to see how it survived the long space 
trip 
experiments on ldef have been subjected to spaces environment 
extreme temperatures a nearvacuum microgravity 
micrometeoroids cosmic radiation corrosive atomic oxygen and 
other things from outer space 
some other experiments aboard include one designed to collect 
interplanetary dust that could reveal information about the sun and 
planets also aboard are 125 million tomato seeds for student 
experiments and research into such things as germination rates 
chromosome and population genetics studies and full tomato growth 
the satellite will be taken to an extremely clean building at 
the kennedy space center for examination by teams expert in 
materials spacecraft systems radiation and space debris the 
experiments will then be distributed to their individual 
investigators 
</TEXT>
