during the onemonth stoppage syria and iraq will get 75 
percent less water from the tributaries of the euphrates the 
1460milelong river that has been the lifeblood throughout 
history for the area once ancient mesopotamia the river already 
slows to become a sluggish stream before joining the tigris at the 
