occurred what the companys response was to protect the 
environment and what is being done to restore the environment epa 
spokeswoman kim helper said her agency was particularly concerned 
that exxon initially estimated only 5000 gallons of oil had 
spilled 
exxon officials originally blamed a faulty leakdetection alarm 
for allowing so much oil to spill undetected but on tuesday they 
revised that assessment saying the device was oversensitive but 
not faulty and said its attorneys advised them not to say anything 
further on the cause 
exxon spokesman phil wetz said the company also would not 
comment on the proposed epa fines or on the new jersey lawsuit 
