a fire at the delaware county daily times 
newspaper caused an estimated 1 million in damages saturday and 
forced editors to print sundays edition at a nearby sister paper 
the fire which broke out in the press room about 245 pm may 
have been caused by roofers using propane torches to repair the 
roof of the suburban philadelphia newspaper office said fire chief 
tom micozzie of the primos secane westbrook park fire co no 5 
the fire was brought under control about 430 pm and is still 
under investigation he said 
two editors and a reporter were inside the building when its 
fire alarms sounded but they escaped without injury 
the newspapers printing press pressroom editorial department 
and a paper storage area received extensive water damage in 
addition the roof of the building will have to be replaced 
micozzie said 
id say were looking at an excess of 1 million in damages 
he said 
much of the water came from the buildings sprinkler system 
which miccozie credited with saving the structure 
kelvyn anderson was one of three staff members working in the 
newsroom when the fire broke out 
the alarm went off and at first we didnt realize it was the 
fire alarm that went off he said 
when they saw smoke coming from the press area anderson said 
he news editor jim atkins and editorial page editor joe monchecurt 
left the building 
