a woman charged with holding her infant son at 
knifepoint during a 14hour standoff with police is incompetent to 
stand trial a jury has ruled 
the state district court jury ruled friday that tracy diane 
levis 24 of houston cannot be tried on aggravated assault charges 
because of mental incompetence 
judge charles hearn ordered ms levis transferred to vernon 
state hospital after a few months psychiatrists will inform hearn 
whether ms levis has regained competence to point of understanding 
legal proceedings against her 
a report by harris county psychiatrist jaime ganc said ms levis 
has been in about a dozen mental hospitals in the past five years 
and suffers from delusions and paranoia the report said she hears 
voices of derogatory content and later identifies the 
voices as belonging to the devil 
ms levis had been traveling in a car with her mother barbara 
levis and her 1yearold son brandon duke on nov 3 1989 when 
she pulled a hunting knife on her mother who was driving the car 
when mrs levis fled the car her daughter reportedly chased her 
and then locked herself inside the car with the baby 
ms levis her face caked with white makeup was holding the 
knife to her sons throat when police arrived she continued to do 
so for 14 hours despite kissing and patting the child in her lap 
during the lengthy ordeal 
the confrontation ended when police exploded a percussion 
grenade near the car distracting the woman while officers rushed 
the car and broke out a window to free the boy and arrest ms levis 
the boy remains in the care of relatives 
