<TEXT>
jerome weinstein the former longtime 
editor of the centre daily times whose journalism career spanned 
more than 50 years has died after suffering a heart attack he was 
73 
weinstein who died friday was editor of the newspaper from 
1945 until his retirement in 1980 he had suffered a heart attack 
at his home in state college on jan 2 
weinstein became sports editor of the times in 1937 a year 
before he graduated from penn state in 1940 he was named city 
editormanaging editor the following year he joined the 
associated press and served as news editor in philadelphia and 
harrisburg 
he rejoined the times in 1945 after editing a newspaper 
distributed from miami beach fla throughout the caribbean 
during his tenure the centre daily times grew from a sixpage 
newspaper with a circulation of 1800 to a 40page newspaper with a 
circulation of more than 20000 the staff increased in size from 
three to 30 
weinstein directed the editorial efforts of the newspaper for 24 
years longer than any other editor of the times or its weekly 
predecessor the state college times 
jerry was the personification of the centre daily times for 
more years than most of its readers have been alive said the 
newspapers editor since weinsteins retirement robert ashley 
he was instrumental in shaping the nucleus of this end of the 
paper and he maintained his passion for it up until the end 
weinstein was president of the pennsylvania society of newspaper 
editors in 1953 and of the associated press managing editors in 
1958 he was a retired member of sigma delta chi the journalism 
honorary society the american society of newspaper editors and the 
national conference of editorial writers 
under his direction the newspaper staff garnered more than 100 
professional awards including five sweepstakes awards the highest 
honor of the pennsylvania newspaper publishers association and the 
pennsylvania society of newspaper editors 
weinstein is survived by his wife thomazine curtin weinstein 
and two daughters 
