for illtimed layoff announcements but he said the hungarian deal 
reflected how the company was seeking to expand in areas of the 
world where the potential for growth is the strongest in the long 
run jouppi said that would benefit gm 
i think in a nutshell were seeing the globalization of the 
entire auto industry he said in the hungaryus situation 
there would not be a conflict creating jobs in hungary and taking 
them away in the united states 
